---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

export const prerender = true;
const updated = "June 16, 2026";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Clad"
  description="How CladFacts (cladfacts.com) handles your information, including optional accounts: no advertising, no analytics, no selling your data."
>
  <article class="static-page">
    <h2 class="static-page__title">Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="dateline">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>CladFacts LLC</strong>
      ("CladFacts," "Clad," "we," "us") handles information in connection with the
      website at <strong>cladfacts.com</strong> (the "Site"). You can read the
      Site without an account. We also offer <strong>optional accounts</strong>
      so you can save preferences and set up topic alerts; this policy explains
      what we collect if you create one.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">The short version</h3>
    <p>
      We run <strong>no advertising, no analytics, and no cross-site trackers</strong>,
      and we <strong>do not sell your personal information</strong>. If you create
      an account, we collect only what's needed to operate it (such as your email).
      You can delete your account and data at any time.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Information we collect</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Reading the Site (no account).</strong> You can browse without
        giving us personal details. Our host processes standard technical request
        data (see "Service providers" below).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Accounts (email sign-up).</strong> If you register with email, we
        store your name, email address, and a securely hashed password. We never
        store your password in readable form.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Accounts (social sign-in).</strong> If you sign in with Google,
        Apple, or X, that provider shares a limited profile with us — typically
        your name, email address, and avatar — which we use to create and identify
        your account. We don't receive your social-media password.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Sessions.</strong> When you're signed in, we store a session
        record and set a secure, strictly-necessary cookie so you stay logged in.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Preferences, saved articles &amp; topic alerts.</strong> If you
        save preferences, opt in to our newsletter, subscribe to alerts for
        certain topics, or save (bookmark) articles, we store those settings and
        saved items on your account so we can apply them and notify you.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Report flags.</strong> If you flag a report's grade or lean, we
        store your comment and which report it concerns so the editor can review
        it. Don't include personal information you don't want retained.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>If you email us.</strong> When you contact
        <a href="mailto:support@cladfacts.com">support@cladfacts.com</a>, we
        receive your message and use it only to respond.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">How we use information</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>To create and secure your account and keep you signed in.</li>
      <li>To send <strong>transactional email</strong> — email verification and password resets, and, if you opt in, the newsletter, digests, and topic alerts you requested.</li>
      <li>To save and apply your preferences and the articles you bookmark.</li>
      <li>To operate, protect, and improve the Site, and to respond to you.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not use your information for advertising, and we do not sell or rent it.</p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Service providers</h3>
    <p>We rely on a small set of vendors that process data on our behalf:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosting and our database (which stores
        account data). Like any host, Cloudflare also processes basic technical
        request data (e.g., IP address, browser type, pages requested) to deliver
        and protect the Site, under its own terms.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Resend</strong> — sends our transactional email (verification,
        password resets, topic alerts). It processes your email address to deliver
        those messages.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google, Apple, and X</strong> — only if you choose to sign in with
        them, and only the profile data described above.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>YouTube / Google</strong> — reports may embed the original source
        video; playing it loads content from YouTube, which may set its own cookies
        under
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Cookies</h3>
    <p>
      We use a <strong>strictly-necessary cookie</strong> to keep you signed in,
      and we may set a basic security/functionality cookie. We set
      <strong>no advertising or analytics cookies</strong> and use no cross-site
      trackers. Embedded YouTube players may set their own cookies when you play a
      video.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Your choices and rights</h3>
    <p>
      You can review or update your account details, sign out, and
      <strong>delete your account</strong> (which removes your associated data) at
      any time — email
      <a href="mailto:support@cladfacts.com">support@cladfacts.com</a> and we'll
      action it. Depending on where you live, you may have additional rights to
      access, correct, or delete your data; contact us to exercise them.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Data retention</h3>
    <p>
      We keep account data while your account is active and delete it on request
      or within a reasonable period after account closure, except where we must
      retain limited records to meet legal obligations or prevent abuse.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Payments (future)</h3>
    <p>
      CladFacts is free today. If we introduce paid subscriptions, payments will
      be handled by a third-party payment processor, and we will not store full
      card numbers. We'll update this policy before any paid features launch.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Children</h3>
    <p>
      The Site is intended for a general audience and is not directed to children
      under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information from them. If you
      believe a child has provided us information, contact us and we'll delete it.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Changes</h3>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as the Site evolves. Material changes will be
      reflected by the "Last updated" date above.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub" id="contact">Contact</h3>
    <p>
      Questions about privacy? Email
      <a href="mailto:support@cladfacts.com">support@cladfacts.com</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="static-page__note">
      This page is provided for transparency and is not legal advice.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
